    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-boutros-bess-l3vpn-services-over-sr-01.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-boutros-bess-l3vpn-services-over-sr-01.txt</link>
        <title>"A Simplified Scalable L3VPN Service Model with Segment Routing Underlay", Sami Boutros, Siva Sivabalan, Jim Uttaro, Dan Voyer, Bin Wen, Luay Jalil</title>
        <dc:date>2021-10-11T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This document proposes a new approach for realizing classical L3VPN (vpnv4/vpnv6/6PE/6VPE) over Segment Routing (SR) networks.  It significantly improves scalability and convergence of the L3VPN control plane.  Furthermore, it naturally brings the benefits of All- Active multi-homing support to the classical L3VPN.</description>
    </item>
